RESEARCH CAPSTONE
Notes: HIST 4900 is the history capstone research seminar. In fall 2019, the seminar will focus on the history of port communities and dock workers as a way to introduce students to the tools, methodologies, and questions of transnational, global, and labor history.

Title: RESEARCH CAPSTONE
Notes: Human beings (and all living creatures on this planet) share one indisputable, unavoidable truth: we will all die. Considering the universality of this fact, we know very little about how humans have dealt with death across time and space, including the material and narrative cultures about death and dying. This course seeks to address this historiographic silence through joint readings and individual research, culminating in an article length research paper and oral presentation.
